  <p class="about-back"><a href="/about-me">← About me</a></p>

  <h1 class="about-subheading">Life</h1>

  <p>
    Filippo was born in Fabriano on the last Sunday of September 1995.
    Restless even as a child, it took the 1997 earthquake to get him to sleep.
    He grew up surrounded by love, playing with Lego and letting his
    imagination run wild amongst the hills of
    <a href="https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marischio">Marischio</a>, to the
    sound of cicadas in summer and the howling wind in winter.
  </p>

  <p>
    At the age of four, he broke his right collarbone and developed an
    inguinal hernia from doing too many somersaults. The smell of coffee used
    to excite him greatly, turning him into a sort of Obelix on the magic
    potion. Today, he is a keen coffee drinker.
  </p>

  <p>
    Curious and restless from childhood, he showed an early interest in the
    natural sciences, saying he wanted to become a scientist. Over time, his
    ambitions changed moving from being a paleoanthropologist (aged 8), a
    musicologist (aged 13), an Orchestra director (aged 14) and a basketball
    player (aged 15).
  </p>

  <p>
    He tested love for the first time at the age of eight, and from that
    moment on, the feelings of love and affection would accompany him
    throughout his life, evolving from the sweetness of youth to the
    bittersweetness of maturity.
  </p>

  <p>
    He actively partecipated to the local scout community (Fabriano 1) from
    the age of 8 until 24, partecipating at the world scout Jamboree in 2011
    in Sweden as part of the italian contigent.
  </p>

  <p>
    He has lived in Italy, the Czech Republic, Finland, Germany, Spain and
    Switzerland.
  </p>

  <p>
    Filippo speaks fluently Italian, English and Spanish and he has been
    trying to learn German for years with little success.
  </p>

  <p>
    He would later say that it was at University and through his studies that
    he found the key to his emancipation and happiness.
  </p>
